label: developmentally replaces
definition: x developmentally replaces y if and only if there is some developmental process that causes x to move or to cease to exist, and for the site that was occupied by x to become occupied by y, where y either comes into existence in this site or moves to this site from somewhere else
classAxiomExampleUsage: metanephros **SubClassOf** developmentally replaces **some** mesonephros|tympanic cavity **SubClassOf** developmentally replaces **some** tubotympanic recess lumen|lumen of pharyngotympanic tube **SubClassOf** developmentally replaces **some** tubotympanic recess lumen|endochondral bone **SubClassOf** developmentally replaces **some** cartilage tissue|oronasal cavity **SubClassOf** developmentally replaces **some** oronasal membrane

label: developmentally succeeded by
definition: Inverse of developmentally preceded by

label: evolutionarily related to
definition: A relationship that holds via some environmental process

label: ecologically related to
definition: A relationship that is mediated in some way by the environment or environmental feature (ENVO:00002297)

label: confers advantage in
classAxiomExampleUsage: fin **SubClassOf** confers advantage in **some** aquatic biome|nasal tentacle **SubClassOf** confers advantage in **some** subterrestrial habitat|gill **SubClassOf** confers advantage in **some** aquatic biome|wing **SubClassOf** confers advantage in **some** aerial habitat|salt gland **SubClassOf** confers advantage in **some** marine biome

label: mereotopologically related to
definition: A mereological relationship or a topological relationship

label: member of
definition: is member of is a mereological relation between a item and a collection.

label: has member
definition: has member is a mereological relation between a collection and an item.
classAxiomExampleUsage: collection of feathers **EquivalentTo** anatomical cluster **and** has member **some** feather|collection of hair on face **SubClassOf** has member **some** strand of hair of face|collection of eyelashes **EquivalentTo** collection of hair on face **and** has member **some** eyelash|collection of hairs **EquivalentTo** anatomical cluster **and** has member **some** strand of hair

label: attached to
classAxiomExampleUsage: rectus thoracis muscle **SubClassOf** attached to **some** rib|central tendon of diaphragm **SubClassOf** attached to **some** fibrous pericardium|palatal tooth **EquivalentTo** calcareous tooth **and** attached to **some** palate bone|eyelash **SubClassOf** attached to **some** eyelid|lower jaw molar **SubClassOf** attached to **some** dentary

label: has muscle origin
classAxiomExampleUsage: brachioradialis **SubClassOf** has muscle origin **some** humerus|frontalis **SubClassOf** has muscle origin **some** epicranial aponeurosis|iliofemoralis muscle **EquivalentTo** muscle of pelvis **and** has muscle origin **some** ilium **and** has muscle insertion **some** femur|puboischiofemoralis internus muscle **SubClassOf** has muscle origin **some** lumbar vertebra|depressor septi nasi **SubClassOf** has muscle origin **some** maxilla

label: has muscle insertion
classAxiomExampleUsage: iliofemoralis muscle **EquivalentTo** muscle of pelvis **and** has muscle origin **some** ilium **and** has muscle insertion **some** femur|quadriceps femoris **SubClassOf** has muscle insertion **some** tibia|fibularis longus **SubClassOf** has muscle insertion **some** metatarsal bone of digit 1|cremaster muscle **SubClassOf** has muscle insertion **some** tunica vaginalis testis|depressor labii inferioris **SubClassOf** has muscle insertion **some** orbicularis oris muscle

label: has fused element
classAxiomExampleUsage: tibiofibula **SubClassOf** has fused element **some** fibula|coccyx **SubClassOf** has fused element **some** coccygeal vertebra|postorbital bar **SubClassOf** has fused element **some** zygomatic process of frontal bone|radio-ulna **SubClassOf** has fused element **some** ulna|radio-ulna **SubClassOf** has fused element **some** radius bone

label: tributary of
definition: x tributary_of y if and only if x a channel for the flow of a substance into y, where y is larger than x. If x and y are hydrographic features, then y is the main stem of a river, or a lake or bay, but not the sea or ocean. If x and y are anatomical, then y is a vein.
classAxiomExampleUsage: median cubital vein **SubClassOf** tributary of **some** basilic vein|external jugular vein **SubClassOf** tributary of **some** subclavian vein|cephalic vein **SubClassOf** tributary of **some** subclavian vein|proper palmar digital vein **SubClassOf** tributary of **some** common palmar digital vein|anterior jugular vein **SubClassOf** tributary of **some** subclavian vein

label: branching part of
definition: x is a branching part of y if and only if x is part of y and x is a branch_of the main stem of y
classAxiomExampleUsage: masseteric nerve **SubClassOf** branching part of **some** mandibular nerve|inferior phrenic artery **SubClassOf** branching part of **some** abdominal aorta|inferior branch of oculomotor nerve **EquivalentTo** nerve **and** supplies **some** inferior rectus extraocular muscle **and** branching part of **some** oculomotor nerve|superior branch of oculomotor nerve **EquivalentTo** nerve **and** supplies **some** superior rectus extraocular muscle **and** branching part of **some** oculomotor nerve|ethmoidal artery **SubClassOf** branching part of **some** ophthalmic artery

label: has developmental potential involving
definition: x has developmental potential involving y iff x is capable of a developmental process with output y. y may be the successor of x, or may be a different structure in the vicinity (as for example in the case of developmental induction).

label: has potential to developmentally contribute to
classAxiomExampleUsage: fin field **EquivalentTo** paired limb/fin field **and** has potential to developmentally contribute to **some** paired fin bud|mesencephalic neural crest **EquivalentTo** neural crest **and** has potential to developmentally contribute to **some** midbrain|diencephalon neural crest **EquivalentTo** neural crest **and** has potential to developmentally contribute to **some** diencephalon|telencephalon neural crest **EquivalentTo** neural crest **and** has potential to developmentally contribute to **some** telencephalon|paired limb/fin field **EquivalentTo** primordium **and** has potential to developmentally contribute to **some** paired limb/fin bud

label: has potential to developmentally induce
definition: x has potential to developmentally induce y iff x developmentally induces y or x is capable of developmentally inducing y

label: has potential to develop into
classAxiomExampleUsage: presumptive bulbus arteriosus **EquivalentTo** presumptive structure **and** has potential to develop into **some** bulbus arteriosus|sublingual gland primordium **SubClassOf** has potential to develop into **some** sublingual gland|submandibular gland primordium **SubClassOf** has potential to develop into **some** submandibular gland|proctodeum **SubClassOf** has potential to develop into **some** anal region|future nucleus ambiguus **EquivalentTo** gray matter of neuraxis **and** has potential to develop into **some** nucleus ambiguus

label: has potential to directly develop into
produces
definition: a produces b if some process that occurs_in a has_output b, where a and b are material entities. Examples: hybridoma cell line produces monoclonal antibody reagent; chondroblast produces avascular GAG-rich matrix.
classAxiomExampleUsage: salivary gland **EquivalentTo** gland **and** produces **some** saliva|silk gland **EquivalentTo** gland **and** produces **some** silk|ciliary epithelium **SubClassOf** produces **some** aqueous humor of eyeball|sweat gland **EquivalentTo** gland **and** produces **some** sweat|mucous gland **SubClassOf** produces **some** mucus

label: produced by
classAxiomExampleUsage: scrotal sweat **EquivalentTo** sweat **and** produced by **some** scrotal sweat gland|sweat of axilla **EquivalentTo** sweat **and** produced by **some** axilla|bulbourethral gland secretion **EquivalentTo** bodily secretion **and** produced by **some** bulbo-urethral gland|colostrum **SubClassOf** produced by **some** mammary gland|milk **SubClassOf** produced by **some** mammary gland

label: connected to
definition: Binary relationship: x connected_to y if and only if there exists some z such that z connects x and y in a ternary connected_to(x,y,z) relationship.
classAxiomExampleUsage: metatarsal bone **SubClassOf** connected to **some** tarsal bone|metatarsal bone **SubClassOf** connected to **some** phalanx of pes|lateroobronchus **SubClassOf** connected to **some** posterior thoracic air sac|radial sesamoid **SubClassOf** connected to **some** metacarpal bone of digit 1|axial skeleton plus cranial skeleton **SubClassOf** connected to **some** appendicular skeleton

label: composed_primarily_of
definition: x composed_primarily_of y iff: more than half of the mass of x is made from parts of y
classAxiomExampleUsage: proximal tarsal bone pre-cartilage condensation **EquivalentTo** proximal tarsal bone endochondral element **and** composed_primarily_of **some** pre-cartilage condensation|distal carpal bone 4 **EquivalentTo** distal carpal bone 4 endochondral element **and** composed_primarily_of **some** bone tissue|proximal carpal bone pre-cartilage condensation **EquivalentTo** proximal carpal endochondral element **and** composed_primarily_of **some** pre-cartilage condensation|distal carpal bone 3 **EquivalentTo** distal carpal bone 3 endochondral element **and** composed_primarily_of **some** bone tissue|distal carpal bone 3 pre-cartilage condensation **EquivalentTo** distal carpal bone 3 endochondral element **and** composed_primarily_of **some** pre-cartilage condensation

label: anteriorly connected to
definition: x anteriorly_connected_to y iff the anterior part of x is connected to y. i.e. x connected_to y and x posterior_to y.
classAxiomExampleUsage: neck **SubClassOf** anteriorly connected to **some** head|mammalian cervical vertebra 3 **SubClassOf** anteriorly connected to **some** vertebral bone 2|thoracic vertebra 10 **SubClassOf** anteriorly connected to **some** thoracic vertebra 9|thoracic vertebra 7 **SubClassOf** anteriorly connected to **some** thoracic vertebra 6|thoracic vertebra 12 **SubClassOf** anteriorly connected to **some** thoracic vertebra 11

label: channel for
classAxiomExampleUsage: mammary duct **SubClassOf** channel for **some** milk|lateral vaginal canal **SubClassOf** channel for **some** semen|blood vessel **SubClassOf** channel for **some** blood|bile duct **EquivalentTo** duct **and** channel for **some** bile|male genital duct **SubClassOf** channel for **some** semen

label: channels_from
classAxiomExampleUsage: posterior cardinal vein **SubClassOf** channels_from **some** vasculature of trunk|ejaculatory duct **SubClassOf** channels_from **some** seminal vesicle|efferent duct **SubClassOf** channels_from **some** rete testis|pulmonary venous system **SubClassOf** channels_from **some** lung vasculature|brachiocephalic artery **SubClassOf** channels_from **some** arch of aorta

label: channels_into
classAxiomExampleUsage: cystic duct **SubClassOf** channels_into **some** common bile duct|rete testis **SubClassOf** channels_into **some** efferent duct|renal pelvis **SubClassOf** channels_into **some** ureter|common bile duct **SubClassOf** channels_into **some** ventral pancreatic duct|ejaculatory duct **SubClassOf** channels_into **some** urethra

label: connects
definition: Binary relationship: z connects x if and only if there exists some y such that z connects x and y in a ternary connected_to(x,y,z) relationship.
classAxiomExampleUsage: bregma **SubClassOf** connects **some** coronal suture|inferior tibiofibular joint **SubClassOf** connects **some** distal epiphysis of fibula|tympanohyoid cartilage **SubClassOf** connects **some** styloid process of temporal bone|talofibular ligament **EquivalentTo** skeletal ligament **and** connects **some** fibula **and** connects **some** talus|intertrochanteric crest **SubClassOf** connects **some** greater trochanter

label: distally connected to
definition: x distally_connected_to y iff the distal part of x is connected to y. i.e. x connected_to y and x proximal_to y.
classAxiomExampleUsage: stylopodial skeleton **and** part_of **some** Tetrapoda **SubClassOf** distally connected to **some** zeugopodial skeleton|distal tarsal bone 2 **SubClassOf** distally connected to **some** metatarsal bone of digit 2|distal tarsal bone 1 **SubClassOf** distally connected to **some** metatarsal bone of digit 1|distal tarsal bone 3 **SubClassOf** distally connected to **some** metatarsal bone of digit 3|middle phalanx **and** part_of **some** Euarchontoglires **SubClassOf** distally connected to **some** distal phalanx

label: enclosed_by
classAxiomExampleUsage: lumen of anal canal **EquivalentTo** anatomical space **and** enclosed_by **some** anal canal|stomach lumen **EquivalentTo** anatomical space **and** enclosed_by **some** stomach|mantle cavity **EquivalentTo** anatomical space **and** enclosed_by **some** mantle|lumen of central canal of spinal cord **EquivalentTo** anatomical space **and** enclosed_by **some** central canal of spinal cord|cavum septum pellucidum **EquivalentTo** anatomical space **and** enclosed_by **some** septum pellucidum

label: encloses
definition: x encloses y iff the convex hull formed by x contains all or the majority of y.
classAxiomExampleUsage: orbital region **SubClassOf** encloses **some** camera-type eye|nasal cartilage **SubClassOf** encloses **some** nasal vestibule|anatomical conduit **SubClassOf** encloses **some** anatomical conduit space|neurocranium **SubClassOf** encloses **some** brain

label: evolved_from
classAxiomExampleUsage: gastrocnemius lateralis **SubClassOf** evolved_from **some** gastrocnemius externus|gastrocnemius medialis **SubClassOf** evolved_from **some** gastrocnemius internus|paired limb/fin **SubClassOf** evolved_from **some** paired fin|spiral organ of cochlea **SubClassOf** evolved_from **some** basilar papilla|snake venom gland **SubClassOf** evolved_from **some** salivary gland

label: evolved_multiple_times_in
classAxiomExampleUsage: vertebral centrum **SubClassOf** evolved_multiple_times_in **some** Vertebrata <Metazoa>|interventricular septum **SubClassOf** evolved_multiple_times_in **some** Vertebrata <Metazoa>

label: existence_ends_at
definition: c existence_ends_at e iff c exists_at e and not ( exists e2 : c exists_at e2 and e before e2).

label: existence_ends_before
definition: Relation between continuant c and occurrent s, such that every instance of c ceases to exist before s.

label: existence_ends_with
definition: Relation between continuant and occurrent, such that c ceases to exist at the end of p.
classAxiomExampleUsage: juvenile organism **EquivalentTo** multi-cellular organism **and** existence_ends_with **some** juvenile stage **and** existence_starts_with **some** juvenile stage|adult organism **EquivalentTo** multi-cellular organism **and** existence_ends_with **some** post-juvenile adult stage **and** existence_starts_with **some** post-juvenile adult stage|cleaving embryo **EquivalentTo** multi-cellular organism **and** existence_ends_with **some** cleavage stage **and** existence_starts_with **some** cleavage stage|conceptus **SubClassOf** existence_ends_with **some** embryo stage|embryo **EquivalentTo** multi-cellular organism **and** existence_ends_with **some** embryo stage **and** existence_starts_with **some** embryo stage

label: existence_starts_after
definition: Relation between continuant c and occurrent s, such that every instance of c comes into existing after some s has completed.

label: existence_starts_and_ends_during
classAxiomExampleUsage: extraembryonic structure **EquivalentTo** anatomical structure **and** adjacent_to **some** embryonic structure **and** existence_starts_and_ends_during **some** embryo stage|tadpole **EquivalentTo** multi-cellular organism **and** existence_starts_and_ends_during **some** tadpole stage|blastula **EquivalentTo** multi-cellular organism **and** existence_starts_and_ends_during **some** blastula stage|echinopluteus larva **EquivalentTo** multi-cellular organism **and** existence_starts_and_ends_during **some** echinopluteus larval stage|nematode larva **EquivalentTo** multi-cellular organism **and** existence_starts_and_ends_during **some** nematode larval stage

label: existence_starts_at
definition: c existence_starts_at e iff c exists_at e and not ( exists e2 : c exists_at e2 and e2 before e)

label: existence_starts_with
definition: Relation between continuant and occurrent, such that c comes into existence at the start of p.
classAxiomExampleUsage: conceptus **SubClassOf** existence_starts_with **some** embryo stage|juvenile organism **EquivalentTo** multi-cellular organism **and** existence_ends_with **some** juvenile stage **and** existence_starts_with **some** juvenile stage|adult organism **EquivalentTo** multi-cellular organism **and** existence_ends_with **some** post-juvenile adult stage **and** existence_starts_with **some** post-juvenile adult stage|cleaving embryo **EquivalentTo** multi-cellular organism **and** existence_ends_with **some** cleavage stage **and** existence_starts_with **some** cleavage stage|post-embryonic organism **EquivalentTo** multi-cellular organism **and** existence_starts_with **some** post-embryonic stage

label: has_end
classAxiomExampleUsage: late embryonic stage **SubClassOf** has_end **some** life cycle stage boundary|life cycle stage **SubClassOf** has_end **some** life cycle stage boundary

label: has_muscle_antagonist
definition: m1 has_muscle_antagonist m2 iff m1 acts in opposition to m2, and m2 is responsible for returning the structure to its initial position.
classAxiomExampleUsage: plantaris **SubClassOf** has_muscle_antagonist **some** tibialis anterior|tibialis anterior **SubClassOf** has_muscle_antagonist **some** tibialis posterior|latissimus dorsi muscle **SubClassOf** has_muscle_antagonist **some** deltoid|adductor pollicis muscle **SubClassOf** has_muscle_antagonist **some** abductor pollicis brevis muscle|flexor pollicis longus muscle **SubClassOf** has_muscle_antagonist **some** extensor pollicis longus muscle

label: has_start
classAxiomExampleUsage: life cycle stage **SubClassOf** has_start **some** life cycle stage boundary

label: output_of
classAxiomExampleUsage: intramembranous bone **SubClassOf** output_of **some** intramembranous ossification|membrane bone **SubClassOf** output_of **some** intramembranous ossification|cud **EquivalentTo** bolus of food **and** output_of **some** rumination|intramembranous bone tissue **EquivalentTo** bone tissue **and** output_of **some** intramembranous ossification|endochondral bone tissue **EquivalentTo** bone tissue **and** output_of **some** endochondral ossification

label: posteriorly connected to
definition: x posteriorly_connected_to y iff the posterior part of x is connected to y. i.e. x connected_to y and x anterior_to y.
classAxiomExampleUsage: neck **SubClassOf** posteriorly connected to **some** trunk

label: proximally connected to
definition: x proximally_connected_to y iff the proximal part of x is connected to y. i.e. x connected_to y and x distal_to y.
classAxiomExampleUsage: metacarpus skeleton **SubClassOf** proximally connected to **some** carpal skeleton|respiratory bronchiole **SubClassOf** proximally connected to **some** terminal bronchiole|metatarsus skeleton **SubClassOf** proximally connected to **some** tarsal skeleton|metapodial skeleton **SubClassOf** proximally connected to **some** mesopodial skeleton|acropodial skeleton **SubClassOf** proximally connected to **some** metapodial skeleton

label: site_of
definition: C site_of P iff exists species S such that P occurs_in C for all members of S. Example: bursa of Fabricius site_of B-cell differentiation.
classAxiomExampleUsage: postnatal subventricular zone **SubClassOf** site_of **some** neurogenesis|uterus or analog **EquivalentTo** subdivision of tube **and** site_of **some** embryo development|Peyer's patch germinal center **SubClassOf** site_of **some** plasma cell differentiation|vascular cord **SubClassOf** site_of **some** branching morphogenesis of an epithelial tube|gonad **SubClassOf** site_of **some** gamete generation

label: subdivision of
classAxiomExampleUsage: metacarpus skeleton **EquivalentTo** subdivision of skeleton **and** subdivision of **some** metacarpus region|pectoral fin skeleton **EquivalentTo** subdivision of skeleton **and** subdivision of **some** pectoral fin|pelvic fin skeleton **EquivalentTo** subdivision of skeleton **and** subdivision of **some** pelvic fin|forelimb skeleton **EquivalentTo** subdivision of skeleton **and** subdivision of **some** forelimb|hindlimb skeleton **EquivalentTo** subdivision of skeleton **and** subdivision of **some** hindlimb

label: has_quality
classAxiomExampleUsage: lumen of epithelial sac **SubClassOf** has_quality **some** closed|tube **SubClassOf** has_quality **some** cylindrical|hyaloid cavity **SubClassOf** has_quality **some** closed|larva **SubClassOf** has_quality **some** larval|sweat gland **SubClassOf** has_quality **some** cylindrical

label: transformation_of
classAxiomExampleUsage: foramen cecum of tongue **SubClassOf** transformation_of **some** future foramen cecum|uterus **SubClassOf** transformation_of **some** embryonic uterus|lamina terminalis of cerebral hemisphere **SubClassOf** transformation_of **some** lamina terminalis of neural tube

label: immediate_transformation_of
classAxiomExampleUsage: dorsal motor nucleus of vagus nerve **SubClassOf** immediate_transformation_of **some** future dorsal motor nucleus of vagus|inferior salivatory nucleus **SubClassOf** immediate_transformation_of **some** future inferior salivatory nucleus|diaphragm **SubClassOf** immediate_transformation_of **some** future diaphragm|nucleus ambiguus **SubClassOf** immediate_transformation_of **some** future nucleus ambiguus|tongue **SubClassOf** immediate_transformation_of **some** future tongue
